&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post: Registered Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band: 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base Outpatient Department, Royal Gwent hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 2 posts at 32 hours per week and 36 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Scheduled Care Division at the Royal Gwent Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated, dynamic and forward thinking experienced nurse with excellent clinical and interpersonal skills to join our friendly outpatient team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to providing safe and high quality patient care for patients passing through the department, and we provide support to both unscheduled a scheduled care teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to support junior colleague’s essential. The successful applicant must be committed to improving the patient experience and ensuring the high standards that we expect for our patients needs are met. You will be expected to have the flexibility to work within all areas of the department and full training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy being a member of a pro-active nursing team and you are motivated and dedicated to delivering quality care them we would like to hear from you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
